{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-blog-details-js","path":"/blog/dev-containers-new-era-in-development/","result":{"data":{"bloggerPost":{"slug":"dev-containers-new-era-in-development","id":"b66b989d-ed8d-553a-8749-8c7fcd502006","title":"Dev Containers: A New Era in Development Environment","content":"<p>&nbsp;</p><div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgCVeREHO4HlZ8Fvn5x2alqkPKtWH5fxWPcEDeWFunhG5JOalaUzNmPbFyJYXmIfCtGSOFs4wM12KqKIVnt3lknGcBO5in-csQeSQ0TNtljAAIwvyhSoxq7AhsNVVROW5IadwfrTVZ542kNJSo8FBGIFreo3IoSxfhQgGUolaoLQtX9bBqcy4gUAKz8ffA/s535/devops.webp\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" data-original-height=\"377\" data-original-width=\"535\" height=\"258\" src=\"https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgCVeREHO4HlZ8Fvn5x2alqkPKtWH5fxWPcEDeWFunhG5JOalaUzNmPbFyJYXmIfCtGSOFs4wM12KqKIVnt3lknGcBO5in-csQeSQ0TNtljAAIwvyhSoxq7AhsNVVROW5IadwfrTVZ542kNJSo8FBGIFreo3IoSxfhQgGUolaoLQtX9bBqcy4gUAKz8ffA/w407-h258/devops.webp\" width=\"407\" /></a></div><br /><p style=\"clear: both; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"background-color: white; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; text-align: left;\">Ever found yourself in the twilight zone of coding, where your code runs like a dream on your local machine but throws a tantrum in the actual environment? Ah, the classic “</span><span class=\"mw gu\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.003em; text-align: left;\"><em class=\"ns\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">it works on my machine</em></span><span style=\"background-color: white; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; text-align: left;\">” syndrome! We’ve all been there, haven’t we? Diving deep into the abyss of debugging, only to discover that the culprit was a sneaky dependency mismatch. The joys of being a developer, right?</span></p><div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"background-color: white; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; text-align: left;\">Here comes our savior to help us with this: ‘</span><span class=\"mw gu\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.003em; text-align: left;\">Dev Containers</span><span style=\"background-color: white; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; text-align: left;\">’</span></div><h1 class=\"nt nu gt be nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"0bcd\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: sohne, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.016em; line-height: 30px; margin: 1.95em 0px -0.28em;\">Introduction</h1><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx or mz na nb os nd ne nf ot nh ni nj ou nl nm nn ov np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"6ffd\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 0.94em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\">In the wild jungle of software development, a new species has emerged, rising above the rest in its versatility and adaptability. Meet the Dev Containers, the Swiss Army knife of development environments. They’re like a genie in a bottle (or rather, a Docker container), ready to grant your every development wish!</p><h1 class=\"nt nu gt be nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"9088\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: sohne, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.016em; line-height: 30px; margin: 1.95em 0px -0.28em;\">What are Dev Containers?</h1><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx or mz na nb os nd ne nf ot nh ni nj ou nl nm nn ov np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"41e3\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 0.94em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\">Dev Containers are like your personal butler, serving you everything you need for your development work on a silver platter. They’re Docker containers equipped with all the tools, dependencies, and even the code editor you need. No more “it works on my machine” excuses because now everyone’s machine is the same!</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx or mz na nb os nd ne nf ot nh ni nj ou nl nm nn ov np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"41e3\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 0.94em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\"><br /></p><div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgOiAJMIAaLB7s3M5cCzBfRyk4RORQgX1v9OQ3-5gOs9gf_VcndviQmEHf9MhuoyDZf2IGvP3lavOMEpAxnAdrxKScdW3xpzPzr3hAqBryz-sAvV5Fr88aJR8JGlQYrB-rMLnCji29Yv9zM95rnmUpjgAr_u32EmaMtDZxPminHXrgUkP_oB6UHstXRaxw/s500/0_i8hhCSd8RIWEtNP9.webp\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" data-original-height=\"334\" data-original-width=\"500\" height=\"214\" src=\"https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgOiAJMIAaLB7s3M5cCzBfRyk4RORQgX1v9OQ3-5gOs9gf_VcndviQmEHf9MhuoyDZf2IGvP3lavOMEpAxnAdrxKScdW3xpzPzr3hAqBryz-sAvV5Fr88aJR8JGlQYrB-rMLnCji29Yv9zM95rnmUpjgAr_u32EmaMtDZxPminHXrgUkP_oB6UHstXRaxw/s320/0_i8hhCSd8RIWEtNP9.webp\" width=\"320\" /></a></div><br /><h1 class=\"nt nu gt be nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"8bbd\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: sohne, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.016em; line-height: 30px; margin: 1.95em 0px -0.28em;\">Why Use Dev Containers?</h1><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx or mz na nb os nd ne nf ot nh ni nj ou nl nm nn ov np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"5393\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 0.94em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\">Dev Containers are like the superheroes of the development world:</p><ol style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; list-style: none none; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><li class=\"mu mv gt mw b mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no np nq nr pc pd pe bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"a3d8\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; list-style-type: decimal; margin-bottom: -0.46em; margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 2.14em; padding-left: 0px;\"><span class=\"mw gu\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700;\">Consistency</span>: They ensure justice by making sure everyone in the team is playing by the same rules.</li><li class=\"mu mv gt mw b mx pf mz na nb pg nd ne nf ph nh ni nj pi nl nm nn pj np nq nr pc pd pe bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"2943\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; list-style-type: decimal; margin-bottom: -0.46em; margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 1.14em; padding-left: 0px;\"><span class=\"mw gu\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700;\">Isolation</span>: They protect your projects from each other, like a superhero protecting the city from villains.</li><li class=\"mu mv gt mw b mx pf mz na nb pg nd ne nf ph nh ni nj pi nl nm nn pj np nq nr pc pd pe bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"2de5\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; list-style-type: decimal; margin-bottom: -0.46em; margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 1.14em; padding-left: 0px;\"><span class=\"mw gu\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700;\">Reproducibility</span>: They can clone themselves faster than a speeding bullet, making it easy to replicate your development environment.</li><li class=\"mu mv gt mw b mx pf mz na nb pg nd ne nf ph nh ni nj pi nl nm nn pj np nq nr pc pd pe bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"c1f4\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; list-style-type: decimal; margin-bottom: -0.46em; margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 1.14em; padding-left: 0px;\"><span class=\"mw gu\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700;\">Automation</span>: They can set up your development environment in a flash, saving the day by saving you time.</li></ol><h1 class=\"nt nu gt be nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"c7b0\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: sohne, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.016em; line-height: 30px; margin: 1.95em 0px -0.28em;\">Prerequisites for Dev Containers</h1><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx or mz na nb os nd ne nf ot nh ni nj ou nl nm nn ov np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"ec17\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 0.94em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\">Before you can start using Dev Containers, you need to have certain prerequisites in place:</p><ol style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; list-style: none none; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><li class=\"mu mv gt mw b mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no np nq nr pc pd pe bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"e92e\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; list-style-type: decimal; margin-bottom: -0.46em; margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 2.14em; padding-left: 0px;\"><span class=\"mw gu\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700;\">Docker</span>: You need Docker installed and running on your machine. After all, Dev Containers are Docker containers.</li><li class=\"mu mv gt mw b mx pf mz na nb pg nd ne nf ph nh ni nj pi nl nm nn pj np nq nr pc pd pe bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"86c1\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; list-style-type: decimal; margin-bottom: -0.46em; margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 1.14em; padding-left: 0px;\"><span class=\"mw gu\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700;\">VS Code</span>: You need Visual Studio Code, which has built-in support for Dev Containers. It’s like the Batmobile of code editors.</li><li class=\"mu mv gt mw b mx pf mz na nb pg nd ne nf ph nh ni nj pi nl nm nn pj np nq nr pc pd pe bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"2c3c\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; list-style-type: decimal; margin-bottom: -0.46em; margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 1.14em; padding-left: 0px;\"><span class=\"mw gu\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700;\">Remote — Containers extension</span>: This VS Code extension is what allows you to open any folder inside a Dev Container.</li></ol><h1 class=\"nt nu gt be nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"e18e\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: sohne, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.016em; line-height: 30px; margin: 1.95em 0px -0.28em;\">Tools that Support Dev Containers</h1><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx or mz na nb os nd ne nf ot nh ni nj ou nl nm nn ov np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"699f\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 0.94em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\">Currently, Visual Studio Code is the main IDE that supports Dev Containers out of the box with its Remote — Containers extension. However, the concept of containerized development environments is catching on, and we might see more IDEs supporting this in the future.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"295b\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 2.14em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\">Follow this link for more Information —&nbsp;<a class=\"af pk\" href=\"https://containers.dev/supporting\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; box-sizing: inherit;\" target=\"_blank\">https://containers.dev/supporting</a></p><h1 class=\"nt nu gt be nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"5e4d\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: sohne, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.016em; line-height: 30px; margin: 1.95em 0px -0.28em;\">Use Cases</h1><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx or mz na nb os nd ne nf ot nh ni nj ou nl nm nn ov np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"e773\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 0.94em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\">Let’s look at some use cases of how you can use Dev Containers in different scenarios:</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx or mz na nb os nd ne nf ot nh ni nj ou nl nm nn ov np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"e773\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 0.94em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\"><span class=\"mw gu\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.06px;\">Node.js Development:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.06px;\">You can set up a Dev Container with Node.js, npm, and your favorite code editor installed. You can also include a&nbsp;</span><code class=\"cw pl pm pn po b\" style=\"background-color: #f2f2f2; box-sizing: inherit; font-family: source-code-pro, Menlo, Monaco, &quot;Courier New&quot;, Courier, monospace; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: -0.06px; padding: 2px 4px;\">.nvmrc</code><span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.06px;\">&nbsp;file to specify the Node.js version, ensuring everyone is using the same version.</span></p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx or mz na nb os nd ne nf ot nh ni nj ou nl nm nn ov np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"e773\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 0.94em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.06px;\"><br /></span></p><pre style=\"background: rgb(238, 238, 238); border-bottom-color: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-image: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-radius: 10px; border-right-color: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); border-top-style: solid; border-width: 5px 0px 0px; font-stretch: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin-bottom: 1.5em; margin-top: 0px; overflow-wrap: normal; overflow: auto; padding: 12px; vertical-align: baseline;\"><div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both;\"><span style=\"color: #444444; font-family: Courier New, Courier, monospace;\">{\n \"name\": \"My Dev Container\",\n \"build\": {\n \"dockerfile\": \"Dockerfile\",\n \"context\": \"..\",\n \"args\": { \"VARIANT\": \"3\" }\n },\n \"runArgs\": [ \"-u\", \"python\" ],\n \"settings\": { \n\"terminal.integrated.shell.linux\": \"/bin/bash\"\n },\n \"extensions\": [\"ms-python.python\"],\n \"postCreateCommand\": \"echo 'Welcome to your Dev Container!'\",\n \"features\": {\n \"github\": \"insiders\"\n },\n \"forwardPorts\": [5000],\n \"containerEnv\": {\n \"MY_ENV_VAR\": \"my-value\"\n },\n \"remoteUser\": \"python\"\n}</span></div></pre><p><span class=\"mw gu\" face=\"source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.06px;\">Multi-Service Applications:</span><span face=\"source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif\" style=\"background-color: white; color: #242424; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.06px;\">&nbsp;If your application consists of multiple services (e.g., a front-end and a back-end), you can use Docker Compose to define multiple containers and include a&nbsp;</span><code class=\"cw pl pm pn po b\" style=\"background-color: #f2f2f2; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-code-pro, Menlo, Monaco, &quot;Courier New&quot;, Courier, monospace; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: -0.06px; padding: 2px 4px;\">devcontainer.json</code><span face=\"source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif\" style=\"background-color: white; color: #242424; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.06px;\">&nbsp;file to specify how they should be set up.</span></p>\n<pre style=\"background: rgb(238, 238, 238); border-bottom-color: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-image: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-radius: 10px; border-right-color: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); border-top-style: solid; border-width: 5px 0px 0px; font-stretch: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin-bottom: 1.5em; margin-top: 0px; overflow-wrap: normal; overflow: auto; padding: 12px; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"color: #444444; font-family: Courier New, Courier, monospace;\">{\n    \"name\": \"Multi-Service Application\",\n    \"dockerComposeFile\": \"docker-compose.yml\",\n    \"service\": \"app\",\n    \"workspaceFolder\": \"/workspace\",\n    \"extensions\": [\"dbaeumer.vscode-eslint\"],\n    \"postCreateCommand\": \"npm install\",\n    \"forwardPorts\": [3000, 5000],\n    \"containerEnv\": {\n        \"NODE_ENV\": \"development\"\n    },\n    \"remoteUser\": \"node\"\n}</span></pre><p><span class=\"mw gu\" face=\"source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.06px;\">Testing Across Different Environments:</span><span face=\"source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif\" style=\"background-color: white; color: #242424; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.06px;\">&nbsp;You can have multiple&nbsp;</span><code class=\"cw pl pm pn po b\" style=\"background-color: #f2f2f2; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-code-pro, Menlo, Monaco, &quot;Courier New&quot;, Courier, monospace; font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: -0.06px; padding: 2px 4px;\">devcontainer.json</code><span face=\"source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif\" style=\"background-color: white; color: #242424; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.06px;\">&nbsp;files, each specifying a different environment (e.g., different versions of a language or library), allowing you to test your application across different environments easily.</span></p>\n<pre style=\"background: rgb(238, 238, 238); border-bottom-color: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-image: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-radius: 10px; border-right-color: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); border-top-style: solid; border-width: 5px 0px 0px; font-stretch: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin-bottom: 1.5em; margin-top: 0px; overflow-wrap: normal; overflow: auto; padding: 12px; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"color: #444444; font-family: Courier New, Courier, monospace;\">{\n    \"name\": \"Python 3\",\n    \"build\": {\n        \"dockerfile\": \"Dockerfile\",\n        \"context\": \"..\",\n        \"args\": { \"VARIANT\": \"3\" }\n    },\n    \"runArgs\": [ \"-u\", \"python\" ],\n    \"settings\": { \n        \"terminal.integrated.shell.linux\": \"/bin/bash\"\n    },\n    \"extensions\": [\"ms-python.python\"]\n}</span></pre><pre style=\"background: rgb(238, 238, 238); border-bottom-color: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-image: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-radius: 10px; border-right-color: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); border-top-style: solid; border-width: 5px 0px 0px; font-stretch: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-numeric: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin-bottom: 1.5em; margin-top: 0px; overflow-wrap: normal; overflow: auto; padding: 12px; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"color: #444444; font-family: Courier New, Courier, monospace;\">{\n    \"name\": \"Python 2\",\n    \"build\": {\n        \"dockerfile\": \"Dockerfile\",\n        \"context\": \"..\",\n        \"args\": { \"VARIANT\": \"2\" }\n    },\n    \"runArgs\": [ \"-u\", \"python\" ],\n    \"settings\": { \n        \"terminal.integrated.shell.linux\": \"/bin/bash\"\n    },\n    \"extensions\": [\"ms-python.python\"]\n}</span></pre><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"15df\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 2.14em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\">In this example, you can set the `VARIANT` argument to install different Python versions.</p><h1 class=\"nt nu gt be nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"59c2\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: sohne, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.016em; line-height: 30px; margin: 1.95em 0px -0.28em;\">Conclusion</h1><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx or mz na nb os nd ne nf ot nh ni nj ou nl nm nn ov np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"4052\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 0.94em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\">Dev Containers are revolutionizing the way we approach software development. They offer a level of flexibility, consistency, and reproducibility that was previously unheard of. Whether you’re a solo developer working on a side project or part of a large team working on a complex application, Dev Containers can make your life easier.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mu mv gt mw b mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no np nq nr gm bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"b931\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; line-height: 32px; margin: 2.14em 0px -0.46em; word-break: break-word;\">Remember, the best way to understand Dev Containers is to dive in and start using them. So why not give it a try on your next project? You might just find it’s the best decision you’ve made for your development workflow!</p><h1 class=\"nt nu gt be nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bj\" data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" id=\"e4f8\" style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: #242424; font-family: sohne, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.016em; line-height: 30px; margin: 1.95em 0px -0.28em;\">References</h1><ul style=\"background-color: white; box-sizing: inherit; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; list-style: none none; margin: 0px; pa